## Capabilities

- Boolean flags
- Percentage rollout
- User targeting
- Environment targeting
- Country targeting

## Usage

```ts
import { featureFlags } from './src/feature-flags/index.js';

const enabled = await featureFlags.isEnabled('new-checkout', {
  userId: 'beta-user',
  environment: 'staging',
  country: 'US',
});
```

## Providers

| Provider | Class | Notes |
|----------|-------|-------|
| database | `DatabaseFeatureFlagProvider` | Local JSON rules (default) |
| launchdarkly | `LaunchDarklyFeatureFlagProvider` | SDK adapter + local fallback |
| unleash | `UnleashFeatureFlagProvider` | Client adapter + local fallback |

Re-run with a different provider:

```bash
my add feature-flags --provider launchdarkly
my add feature-flags --provider unleash
```
